    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The fourth month of the year in the Julian and Gregorian calendars, containing 30 days and falling between March and May. Its name probably derives from the Latin aperire (“to open”), a possible reference to plant buds opening at this time of year in Rome.</Note_Text>
